From: Juergen Gross <jgross@suse.com>
Subject: kABI fix after KVM: x86: Use scratch field in MMIO fragment
 to hold small write values
Patch-mainline: Never, kABI workaround
References: CVE-2026-31588 bsc#1263165

Hide additional field in struct kvm_mmio_fragment from architectures
different from x86. It is needed for x86 only, and kabi checks are
off there for KVM.

Signed-off-by: Juergen Gross <jgross@suse.com>
Reviewed-by: Petr Pavlu <petr.pavlu@suse.com>
---
diff --git a/include/linux/kvm_host.h b/include/linux/kvm_host.h
--- a/include/linux/kvm_host.h
+++ b/include/linux/kvm_host.h
@@ -318,8 +318,10 @@ static inline bool kvm_vcpu_can_poll(ktime_t cur, ktime_t stop)
 struct kvm_mmio_fragment {
 	gpa_t gpa;
 	void *data;
+#ifdef CONFIG_X86
 	u64 val;
+#endif
-	unsigned int len;
+	unsigned len;
 };
 
 struct kvm_vcpu {
-- 
